<br>
I have a brewing of 198, so the tempers are very trivial to me.  I have a pottery of about 165 so crushing the BD's is also trivial.  I am happy to use all three of these skills to make your armor.  If you or someone you know has a brewing or pottery higher than mine, I would be happy to include them on that part (less chance of a failure with your materials).<br>
<br>
To clarify, if you bring me the raw materials I will do *all* of the needed combines.  <br>
<br>
To answer your questions: Any Enchanter who has the spell Enchant Brellium (49th level) can enchant the metal.  I usually have to buy the spell for the Chanter because they do not have it, and some have not even known it existed (the spell has a limited use, this is it).  You will need a cleric of Brell to imbue the ruby.<br>
<br>
Tradeskills can be a fun part of the game, and if you are jazzed about smithing then I'll be the first to cheer you on and welcome you to the 'tradeskilling club' <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
